WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.126 align:middle line:90%


00:00:05.126 --> 00:00:06.060 align:middle line:90%
>>[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:06.060 --> 00:00:07.612 align:middle line:84%
>>And I think many
people today don't

00:00:07.612 --> 00:00:08.820 align:middle line:90%
know what to believe anymore.

00:00:08.820 --> 00:00:10.632 align:middle line:84%
>>People are basically
going to keep on

00:00:10.632 --> 00:00:13.290 align:middle line:84%
to help uncover what
really happened.

00:00:13.290 --> 00:00:15.680 align:middle line:84%
>>It felt like something
was watching me.

00:00:15.680 --> 00:00:17.690 align:middle line:84%
>>We weren't given
all the information.

00:00:17.690 --> 00:00:19.600 align:middle line:84%
We weren't told
the entire story.

00:00:19.600 --> 00:00:26.940 align:middle line:90%


00:00:26.940 --> 00:00:30.325 align:middle line:10%
>>Our help is in the
name of the Lord.

00:00:30.325 --> 00:00:32.200 align:middle line:10%
>>FATHER HALLORAN: Who
made heaven and earth.

00:00:32.200 --> 00:00:33.280 align:middle line:10%
>>The Lord be with you.

00:00:33.280 --> 00:00:35.680 align:middle line:10%
>>FATHER HALLORAN: May
He also be with you.

00:00:35.680 --> 00:00:37.655 align:middle line:10%
>>[GROWLS]

00:00:37.655 --> 00:00:38.155 align:middle line:10%


00:00:38.155 --> 00:00:40.630 align:middle line:10%
>>FATHER HALLORAN:
Do you hear that?

00:00:40.630 --> 00:00:41.620 align:middle line:10%
>>Don't listen.

00:00:41.620 --> 00:00:54.985 align:middle line:90%


00:00:54.985 --> 00:00:57.460 align:middle line:10%
>>(SPEAKING IN DEMONIC
VOICE) Remember me, Halloran?

00:00:57.460 --> 00:01:03.895 align:middle line:90%


00:01:03.895 --> 00:01:05.380 align:middle line:90%
>>[YELLS]

00:01:05.380 --> 00:01:06.865 align:middle line:90%


00:01:06.865 --> 00:01:30.121 align:middle line:10%
>>[LATIN SPEECH]

00:01:30.121 --> 00:01:37.700 align:middle line:90%


00:01:37.700 --> 00:01:40.350 align:middle line:10%
>>GEORGE NOORY: Well, that
was an excerpt from the movie,

00:01:40.350 --> 00:01:42.510 align:middle line:10%
"Exorcist House of Evil."

00:01:42.510 --> 00:01:44.980 align:middle line:10%
How would you like to go to
sleep after seeing that movie?

00:01:44.980 --> 00:01:46.000 align:middle line:90%
Kind of chilling.

00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:48.930 align:middle line:84%
The filmmaker, of course,
who put that all together

00:01:48.930 --> 00:01:52.760 align:middle line:84%
is Jeff Lewis from Saint Louis,
one of my neck of the woods,

00:01:52.760 --> 00:01:53.550 align:middle line:90%
of course.

00:01:53.550 --> 00:01:55.752 align:middle line:84%
That was a kind of a
scary scene, Jeffrey.

00:01:55.752 --> 00:01:56.710 align:middle line:90%
>>JEFF LEWIS: Oh, yeah.

00:01:56.710 --> 00:02:00.257 align:middle line:84%
And we were kind of worried
about Hayden, the young boy,

00:02:00.257 --> 00:02:02.340 align:middle line:84%
kind of going through all
that in the actual room.

00:02:02.340 --> 00:02:06.057 align:middle line:10%
So we had prep him and
his mother on the events

00:02:06.057 --> 00:02:08.750 align:middle line:10%
that had taken place, and
assured him that he was OK--

00:02:08.750 --> 00:02:10.070 align:middle line:10%
and his mother that he was OK.

00:02:10.070 --> 00:02:11.900 align:middle line:10%
>>GEORGE: How'd you
find the little guy?

00:02:11.900 --> 00:02:14.740 align:middle line:10%
>>LEWIS: He submitted his
resume and a head shot.

00:02:14.740 --> 00:02:20.220 align:middle line:10%
And he just had such a fantastic
look, as to somebody from 1949,

00:02:20.220 --> 00:02:22.930 align:middle line:10%
and was just a neat little
kid when he came in.

00:02:22.930 --> 00:02:25.280 align:middle line:90%
So we cast him immediately.

00:02:25.280 --> 00:02:27.280 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: I hope he doesn't
have nightmares now.

00:02:27.280 --> 00:02:29.321 align:middle line:84%
>>LEWIS: No, we talked to
him, and he's all good.

00:02:29.321 --> 00:02:29.910 align:middle line:90%
He's fine.

00:02:29.910 --> 00:02:31.660 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: He didn't
answer the phone like,

00:02:31.660 --> 00:02:32.800 align:middle line:84%
(SPEAKING IN GRAVELY VOICE)
what do you want, Jeff?

00:02:32.800 --> 00:02:33.550 align:middle line:90%
>>LEWIS: Nope, no.

00:02:33.550 --> 00:02:34.620 align:middle line:90%
No Redrums, no nothing.

00:02:34.620 --> 00:02:38.470 align:middle line:84%
He's doing good and was
at the premiere last night

00:02:38.470 --> 00:02:40.814 align:middle line:84%
at the Saint Louis Film
Festival and doing good.

00:02:40.814 --> 00:02:41.480 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: Great.

00:02:41.480 --> 00:02:47.920 align:middle line:84%
Lots of interest in evil, "The
Exorcist," stories like that.

00:02:47.920 --> 00:02:49.595 align:middle line:90%
How come it's so big these days?

00:02:49.595 --> 00:02:50.970 align:middle line:84%
>>LEWIS: I think
everybody's kind

00:02:50.970 --> 00:02:53.540 align:middle line:90%
of looking for what's beyond.

00:02:53.540 --> 00:02:58.200 align:middle line:84%
Everybody's always had
that-- does life truly end?

00:02:58.200 --> 00:03:01.420 align:middle line:84%
And I think that looking for
things like that and spirits

00:03:01.420 --> 00:03:03.400 align:middle line:84%
and demons, kind
of proves the fact

00:03:03.400 --> 00:03:07.340 align:middle line:84%
that there's life beyond what
we know in the physical form.

00:03:07.340 --> 00:03:10.800 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: Let's go back and
talk about the actual story

00:03:10.800 --> 00:03:13.100 align:middle line:84%
that the book "The
Exorcist" was written about,

00:03:13.100 --> 00:03:15.650 align:middle line:84%
by William Blatty, and,
of course, the movie

00:03:15.650 --> 00:03:18.280 align:middle line:90%
"The Exorcist" with Linda Blair.

00:03:18.280 --> 00:03:19.460 align:middle line:90%
>>LEWIS: Linda Blair, right.

00:03:19.460 --> 00:03:21.180 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: It was a
real story, wasn't it?

00:03:21.180 --> 00:03:22.540 align:middle line:90%
>>LEWIS: Right, yes.

00:03:22.540 --> 00:03:24.660 align:middle line:90%
The actual events took place.

00:03:24.660 --> 00:03:27.550 align:middle line:90%
They did take some licensing.

00:03:27.550 --> 00:03:30.220 align:middle line:84%
Linda Blair played
the girl, in the film.

00:03:30.220 --> 00:03:30.837 align:middle line:90%
But--

00:03:30.837 --> 00:03:32.420 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: Spins--
I'll always remember

00:03:32.420 --> 00:03:33.340 align:middle line:90%
her head spinning around.

00:03:33.340 --> 00:03:34.180 align:middle line:84%
>>LEWIS: The spinning
head and the pea soup--

00:03:34.180 --> 00:03:35.720 align:middle line:90%
that's the two things.

00:03:35.720 --> 00:03:38.660 align:middle line:84%
But the real case
was a young boy.

00:03:38.660 --> 00:03:41.820 align:middle line:84%
It did start in Maryland,
where he and his family

00:03:41.820 --> 00:03:43.290 align:middle line:90%
saw carvings in his stomach.

00:03:43.290 --> 00:03:46.210 align:middle line:84%
And this all took place after
an aunt, and elderly aunt,

00:03:46.210 --> 00:03:48.130 align:middle line:84%
had given him a Ouija
board for Christmas.

00:03:48.130 --> 00:03:48.854 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: Uh-huh.

00:03:48.854 --> 00:03:50.770 align:middle line:84%
>>LEWIS: She passed away
several months later,

00:03:50.770 --> 00:03:56.050 align:middle line:84%
and that's when she started
speaking to him from beyond.

00:03:56.050 --> 00:03:58.180 align:middle line:84%
Once they got the carving
in the stomach that said,

00:03:58.180 --> 00:04:01.740 align:middle line:84%
"Louis," that drove the family
to come to St. Louis to seek

00:04:01.740 --> 00:04:03.494 align:middle line:90%
help from the Jesuit priests.

00:04:03.494 --> 00:04:05.910 align:middle line:84%
And that's what brought them
to St. Louis and to the house

00:04:05.910 --> 00:04:06.904 align:middle line:90%
in Bel-Nor.

00:04:06.904 --> 00:04:09.320 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: Do you think that
they originally thought either

00:04:09.320 --> 00:04:11.580 align:middle line:84%
the kid was
self-mutilating himself,

00:04:11.580 --> 00:04:14.120 align:middle line:84%
or that somebody else would
have carved that on him?

00:04:14.120 --> 00:04:16.667 align:middle line:84%
>>LEWIS: No, I think back
in 1949, none of that

00:04:16.667 --> 00:04:17.250 align:middle line:90%
was back then.

00:04:17.250 --> 00:04:21.130 align:middle line:84%
I think today, people would look
as if it's a self-mutilation

00:04:21.130 --> 00:04:22.560 align:middle line:90%
or schizophrenia.

00:04:22.560 --> 00:04:26.020 align:middle line:84%
But back in 1949, that really
wasn't-- that wasn't an issue

00:04:26.020 --> 00:04:29.250 align:middle line:84%
and a social issue that I
think people even dealt with.

00:04:29.250 --> 00:04:32.820 align:middle line:84%
It's more of a common thing
today that we look at.

00:04:32.820 --> 00:04:37.822 align:middle line:84%
But back in 1949, it was
more of a spiritual thing.

00:04:37.822 --> 00:04:39.530 align:middle line:84%
The thing that they
did find interesting,

00:04:39.530 --> 00:04:42.860 align:middle line:84%
that the carvings weren't
from an exterior carving,

00:04:42.860 --> 00:04:45.150 align:middle line:84%
they were in an
interior carving--

00:04:45.150 --> 00:04:46.190 align:middle line:90%
coming from the inside.

00:04:46.190 --> 00:04:47.481 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: The inside out, yeah.

00:04:47.481 --> 00:04:50.760 align:middle line:84%
>>LEWIS: So that also takes
it from being the kid doing it

00:04:50.760 --> 00:04:51.260 align:middle line:90%
to himself.

00:04:51.260 --> 00:04:53.176 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: There were a
couple priests involved

00:04:53.176 --> 00:04:54.002 align:middle line:90%
in the exorcist--

00:04:54.002 --> 00:04:54.710 align:middle line:90%
>>LEWIS: Correct.

00:04:54.710 --> 00:04:57.410 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: --and the exorcism.

00:04:57.410 --> 00:05:00.010 align:middle line:90%
One was in St. Louis.

00:05:00.010 --> 00:05:00.690 align:middle line:90%
He died.

00:05:00.690 --> 00:05:02.500 align:middle line:84%
I tried to interview
him years ago.

00:05:02.500 --> 00:05:03.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LEWIS: Father Bowdern?

00:05:03.500 --> 00:05:06.060 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: Yeah, absolutely.

00:05:06.060 --> 00:05:07.360 align:middle line:90%
It was a real story.

00:05:07.360 --> 00:05:11.070 align:middle line:84%
And it really scared
a lot of people.

00:05:11.070 --> 00:05:13.010 align:middle line:84%
They tried to exercise
him in the house,

00:05:13.010 --> 00:05:14.810 align:middle line:90%
and they did work on that.

00:05:14.810 --> 00:05:19.600 align:middle line:84%
But they also moved him to
the old Alexian Brothers

00:05:19.600 --> 00:05:20.895 align:middle line:90%
Hospital in Saint Louis--

00:05:20.895 --> 00:05:21.520 align:middle line:90%
>>LEWIS: Right.

00:05:21.520 --> 00:05:25.280 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: --put him in a
room, and what happened there?

00:05:25.280 --> 00:05:28.190 align:middle line:84%
>>LEWIS: Well, they did-- they
worked on him in the house.

00:05:28.190 --> 00:05:30.690 align:middle line:84%
Things-- once he got
to the house, started

00:05:30.690 --> 00:05:32.800 align:middle line:84%
to intensify to the
point-- and this

00:05:32.800 --> 00:05:34.354 align:middle line:90%
was his aunt and uncle's house.

00:05:34.354 --> 00:05:35.770 align:middle line:84%
So the family--
once things really

00:05:35.770 --> 00:05:38.920 align:middle line:84%
started to intensify-- because
it just wasn't the two priests.

00:05:38.920 --> 00:05:40.300 align:middle line:90%
It was seven, eight priests.

00:05:40.300 --> 00:05:40.935 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: They were all--

00:05:40.935 --> 00:05:43.185 align:middle line:84%
>>LEWIS: They were there all
day long, 24 hours a day,

00:05:43.185 --> 00:05:44.380 align:middle line:90%
in shifts and doing this.

00:05:44.380 --> 00:05:46.970 align:middle line:84%
So once it finally
became so traumatic

00:05:46.970 --> 00:05:48.470 align:middle line:84%
to the rest of the
family members,

00:05:48.470 --> 00:05:50.174 align:middle line:84%
they figured they
had to move him.

00:05:50.174 --> 00:05:52.090 align:middle line:84%
They put him in a private
wing of the hospital

00:05:52.090 --> 00:05:54.470 align:middle line:84%
to where they could
monitor him 24 hours a day

00:05:54.470 --> 00:05:59.250 align:middle line:84%
and have constantly
bombarded by the priests.

00:05:59.250 --> 00:06:03.520 align:middle line:84%
And they finally exorcised
the demon, so they thought,

00:06:03.520 --> 00:06:04.892 align:middle line:90%
out of him.

00:06:04.892 --> 00:06:06.600 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: And then
the hospital comes in.

00:06:06.600 --> 00:06:09.950 align:middle line:84%
>>LEWIS: Well, and then the
hospital shut that wing down.

00:06:09.950 --> 00:06:11.280 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: Yeah.

00:06:11.280 --> 00:06:14.050 align:middle line:84%
>>LEWIS: It hadn't been
opened from the '50s

00:06:14.050 --> 00:06:17.270 align:middle line:84%
until, I believe it was '85
or so, when they tore it down.

00:06:17.270 --> 00:06:18.590 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: And then I think
they've torn the building down.

00:06:18.590 --> 00:06:19.173 align:middle line:90%
>>LEWIS: Yeah.

00:06:19.173 --> 00:06:21.890 align:middle line:84%
And the interesting
story about that

00:06:21.890 --> 00:06:24.542 align:middle line:84%
was, when they went to
knock down the hospital,

00:06:24.542 --> 00:06:26.250 align:middle line:84%
they just went in with
the regular cranes

00:06:26.250 --> 00:06:27.500 align:middle line:90%
and knocked the hospital down.

00:06:27.500 --> 00:06:30.929 align:middle line:84%
That section of hospital
they could not knock down.

00:06:30.929 --> 00:06:32.470 align:middle line:84%
So they had to go
to extreme measures

00:06:32.470 --> 00:06:35.780 align:middle line:84%
to get that particular
section to be knocked down.

00:06:35.780 --> 00:06:38.490 align:middle line:84%
But before they did all that,
they got rid of the furniture.

00:06:38.490 --> 00:06:40.990 align:middle line:84%
And that's when they found
Father Bowdern's diary

00:06:40.990 --> 00:06:44.350 align:middle line:84%
that he was keeping
through the entire process.

00:06:44.350 --> 00:06:46.960 align:middle line:84%
And it was locked
in a desk drawer,

00:06:46.960 --> 00:06:50.350 align:middle line:84%
and that's where they found
the diary-- of which we found

00:06:50.350 --> 00:06:53.300 align:middle line:84%
and used that as a
template for what

00:06:53.300 --> 00:06:56.440 align:middle line:84%
was going on in the house and
the real things that happened.

00:06:56.440 --> 00:06:58.420 align:middle line:84%
So there was no
spinning head, but there

00:06:58.420 --> 00:07:01.190 align:middle line:84%
was levitations
and extreme power

00:07:01.190 --> 00:07:04.880 align:middle line:84%
by this boy and multiple
voices and different voices

00:07:04.880 --> 00:07:05.810 align:middle line:90%
that he wouldn't know.

00:07:05.810 --> 00:07:11.220 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: Did the priest,
in his notes, seem scared?

00:07:11.220 --> 00:07:14.640 align:middle line:84%
>>LEWIS: I think his
faith was tested.

00:07:14.640 --> 00:07:19.710 align:middle line:84%
And he-- in the readings,
it doesn't come off

00:07:19.710 --> 00:07:22.710 align:middle line:84%
that he's scared,
but he's definitely

00:07:22.710 --> 00:07:26.920 align:middle line:84%
worried about the other family
members, as well as the boy.

00:07:26.920 --> 00:07:30.640 align:middle line:84%
Because these are things
that he had not experienced.

00:07:30.640 --> 00:07:33.365 align:middle line:84%
When you start getting
beds levitating and--

00:07:33.365 --> 00:07:33.990 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: Yeah.

00:07:33.990 --> 00:07:35.865 align:middle line:84%
>>LEWIS: There are
stories where the kid just

00:07:35.865 --> 00:07:38.090 align:middle line:84%
used several
fingers to throw off

00:07:38.090 --> 00:07:41.280 align:middle line:90%
grown men against the walls.

00:07:41.280 --> 00:07:43.040 align:middle line:84%
I mean, then it
starts getting to--

00:07:43.040 --> 00:07:43.640 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: Truly amazing.

00:07:43.640 --> 00:07:45.056 align:middle line:84%
>>LEWIS: --something
more powerful

00:07:45.056 --> 00:07:46.310 align:middle line:90%
than just a normal boy.

00:07:46.310 --> 00:07:48.420 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: The little
boy is now an adult.

00:07:48.420 --> 00:07:50.400 align:middle line:90%
I think his name is Roland Doe.

00:07:50.400 --> 00:07:52.400 align:middle line:84%
>>LEWIS: Well, that's the
name that the chruch--

00:07:52.400 --> 00:07:53.870 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: Or is that the John
Doe that they've given him?

00:07:53.870 --> 00:07:55.970 align:middle line:84%
>>LEWIS: Yeah, that's the name
that the church has given him.

00:07:55.970 --> 00:07:58.000 align:middle line:84%
And they've gone to
great pains to keep

00:07:58.000 --> 00:08:00.179 align:middle line:84%
that name disclosed,
because they

00:08:00.179 --> 00:08:01.470 align:middle line:90%
didn't want him to be bothered.

00:08:01.470 --> 00:08:02.920 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: And he's never
gone public, has he?

00:08:02.920 --> 00:08:04.430 align:middle line:90%
>>LEWIS: He's never gone public.

00:08:04.430 --> 00:08:06.721 align:middle line:84%
The only things that we were
able to find out about him

00:08:06.721 --> 00:08:08.754 align:middle line:84%
is that he became a
lawyer in Washington,

00:08:08.754 --> 00:08:09.920 align:middle line:90%
and a very prominent lawyer.

00:08:09.920 --> 00:08:10.629 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: DC?

00:08:10.629 --> 00:08:11.170 align:middle line:90%
>>LEWIS: Yes.

00:08:11.170 --> 00:08:13.920 align:middle line:90%
And his life has been fine.

00:08:13.920 --> 00:08:17.604 align:middle line:84%
There's been no
relapses or recurrences.

00:08:17.604 --> 00:08:19.770 align:middle line:84%
So he's doing, to the best
of everyone's knowledge--

00:08:19.770 --> 00:08:21.070 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: He's going to
become the Antichrist.

00:08:21.070 --> 00:08:21.120 align:middle line:90%
>>LEWIS: Yeah.

00:08:21.120 --> 00:08:21.950 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:08:21.950 --> 00:08:22.783 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: Who knows?

00:08:22.783 --> 00:08:23.960 align:middle line:90%
>>LEWIS: He's doing well.

00:08:23.960 --> 00:08:24.360 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: Who knows?

00:08:24.360 --> 00:08:25.985 align:middle line:84%
>>LEWIS: Stranger
things have happened.

00:08:25.985 --> 00:08:29.631 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: He obviously knows
that he was the little boy who

00:08:29.631 --> 00:08:30.755 align:middle line:90%
went through this exorcism.

00:08:30.755 --> 00:08:31.130 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:08:31.130 --> 00:08:33.338 align:middle line:84%
>>LEWIS: He does know that
he was the little boy that

00:08:33.338 --> 00:08:34.330 align:middle line:90%
went through it.

00:08:34.330 --> 00:08:38.059 align:middle line:84%
And we've-- through research,
we have learned that he

00:08:38.059 --> 00:08:40.270 align:middle line:84%
doesn't really remember
a whole lot about things.

00:08:40.270 --> 00:08:41.590 align:middle line:90%
He remembers bits and pieces.

00:08:41.590 --> 00:08:41.760 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: Really?

00:08:41.760 --> 00:08:43.218 align:middle line:84%
>>LEWIS: It's almost
like, kind of,

00:08:43.218 --> 00:08:45.870 align:middle line:84%
being in a coma, to
where he remembers--

00:08:45.870 --> 00:08:48.420 align:middle line:84%
he fades in and out of
the events that took place

00:08:48.420 --> 00:08:49.800 align:middle line:90%
over those months.

00:08:49.800 --> 00:08:51.790 align:middle line:84%
So during the days, when
things would be quiet,

00:08:51.790 --> 00:08:53.840 align:middle line:84%
he remembers more
times like that.

00:08:53.840 --> 00:08:56.960 align:middle line:84%
When things would start to pick
up with the possession, that's

00:08:56.960 --> 00:09:00.890 align:middle line:84%
kind of when, you know,
his mind would black out,

00:09:00.890 --> 00:09:04.134 align:middle line:84%
and he just kind of has
loss of time and memory

00:09:04.134 --> 00:09:04.800 align:middle line:90%
of those events.

00:09:04.800 --> 00:09:07.000 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: Let's take
another clip from the film.

